sd=Prospect Campaign Design	Design and refine prospect campaign specifications based on their impact	A prospect acquisition campaign is updated to provide amended/improved pricing terms that can be offered to targeted prospects poor take-up rate has been detected for the campaign	This Service Domain designs and refines prospect campaigns (or integrates designs from external campaign specialists). Prospect campaigns target new customer acquisition and are typically proactive (involving prospect targeting, contact and solicitation). Version numbering is used to track the impact of changes made to campaigns over their usage.
sdpath=prospect-campaign-design
crpath=prospect-campaign-specification
crr=Prospect Campaign Specification Instance
mcr=Prospect Campaign Specification
bqs=
CONFIG
ProspectCampaignSpecification	create	Create or register an imported prospect campaign design		createProspectCampaignSpecification		#desc
ProspectCampaignSpecification	update	Update details of a prospect campaign specification or usage record		updateProspectCampaignSpecification		#desc
ProspectCampaignSpecification	control	Control the use of a prospect campaign specification (e.g. suspend pending revision)		controlProspectCampaignSpecification		#desc
ProspectCampaignSpecification	exchange	Accept, reject, etc. a prospect campaign specification		exchangeProspectCampaignSpecification		#desc
ProspectCampaignSpecification	capture	Capture impact feedback against a prospect campaign specification (by version number)		captureProspectCampaignSpecification		#desc
ProspectCampaignSpecification	execute	Execute an automated action for a prospect campaign specification (e.g. confirm eligibility requirements)		executeProspectCampaignSpecification		#desc
ProspectCampaignSpecification	request	Request manual intervention with a prospect campaign specification (e.g. obtain interpretation guidance)		requestProspectCampaignSpecification		#desc
ProspectCampaignSpecification	retrieve	Retrieve details about a prospect campaign specification (e.g. obtain use and impact reports)		retrieveProspectCampaignSpecification		#desc
